ANS(str_cmp([@answer[@perm]]));

@answerp=@answer[@perm];
BEGIN_SOLUTION
$PAR SOLUTION $BR $BR
Draw any closed curve. 
If the line integral along the closed curve appears to be zero
, then the vector field appears to be independent of path. Thus
$BR
1. $answerp[0]  $BR
2. $answerp[1]  $BR
3. $answerp[2]  $BR
4. $answerp[3]  $BR
5. $answerp[4]  $BR
